    \begin{frame}
    \frametitle{Motivation}
    Literature has analyzed how a transition to healthy diets can benefit health, biodiversity, land use, and climate (Lancet-EAT)\\
    \vspace{1cm}
    But...
    \begin{itemize}
        \item it is unclear how this transition will occur
        \item the system-wide effects that could derive from this transition
    \end{itemize}
    \vspace{1cm}
    We'll study the Flexitarian Vegetarian or Vegan (\textbf{\textcolor{mygreen}{FVV}}) diet, ie., a diet encompassed in any of these categories.
    \end{frame}
    
    \begin{frame}
    \frametitle{Objective}
    \begin{enumerate}
        \item Create a model to deal with the uncertainty of the scenario projections
        \item Study the following effects:
            \begin{itemize}
                \setbeamercovered{transparent}
                \item<1,2> \textcolor{mygreen}{SDG 2}: Alimentation
                \only<2>{
                    \begin{itemize}
                        \item Macronutrients consumption
                    \end{itemize}
                }
                \item<1,3> \textcolor{mygreen}{SDG 3}: Health 
                \only<3>{
                    \begin{itemize}
                        \item Premature deaths due to AP
                    \end{itemize}
                }
                \item<1,4> \textcolor{mygreen}{SDG 6}: Water management
                \only<4>{
                    \begin{itemize}
                        \item Water consumption (total)
                        \item Water consumption by crop and livestock
                        \item Irrigated and Rainfed water demand
                    \end{itemize}
                }
                \item<1,5> \textcolor{mygreen}{SDG 13}: Emissions
                \only<5>{
                    \begin{itemize}
                        \item GHG emissions
                        \item CH$_4$ agricultural emissions
                        \item N$_2$O agricultural emissions
                    \end{itemize}
                }
                \item<1,6> \textcolor{mygreen}{SDG 15}: Land use
                \only<6>{
                    \begin{itemize}
                        \item Area of forest, pasture, cropland, and other land
                        \item Re-forestation
                        \item Cropland management (area and fertilizer demand)
                        \item Crop loss due to AP
                        \item Carbon stock
                    \end{itemize}
                }
            \end{itemize}
    \end{enumerate}
    \end{frame}
    
    \begin{frame}
    \frametitle{The model}
        Assumptions \vspace{0.5cm}
        \begin{enumerate}
            \item Each person decides to become FVV independently but is influenced by 3 factors:
                \begin{itemize}
                    \item Social pressure weight
                    \item Percentage of the population following the FVV diet by 2100
                    \item Peak year when the majority of the population will shift
                \end{itemize} \vspace{0.5cm}
            \item Once a person decides to follow the FVV diet, will stick to this decision for the rest of the century
        \end{enumerate}    
    \end{frame}
    
